  "commentary": "With SPX at 6992 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (17.3B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above this level while providing support on dips toward the 6975 level. The PIN regime with 120.7B in total GEX creates a strong mean-reverting environment, particularly given the -2.1% pullback over the last 5 minutes from what was likely a test of the 7000 resistance. Key levels to watch are the 7000 ceiling where dealer selling intensifies, the 6975 support level, and any breakdown toward the 6878 flip point which would shift the hedging dynamics.\n\nBottom line: expect SPX to chop between 6975-7000 with resistance capping upside moves.",
